concert.info: Children under 2 years old do not require a ticket. Interested in Group Tickets? For groups of 15 or more, call the Titans Ticket Office at 615.565.4200.
concert.pleaseNote: There is a 4 ticket limit per game along with a 2 game maximum purchase.

venues.name: Nissan Stadium

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: 615-565-4200. Fax is 615-565-4212. For CMA Festival Info, please call 1-800-CMAFEST
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Discover & Cash.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call begins 2 1/2 hours prior to event.

venues.parkingDetail: Available downtown, public parking garages and lots. Or call the Nashville Public Transportaion MTA department at 615-862-5950.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: This is an accessible venue: All Patrons in Wheelchairs Must Purchase Accessible Seating. For CMA Music Festival: Please contact CMA at 800-262-3378 for accessible seats.

generalInfo.generalRule: Nissan Stadium Clear Bag Policy: Ensuring the safety and security of Nissan Stadium guests is a top priority. Before coming to the game, please familiarize yourself with the NFL’s bag policy that will be strictly enforced at the gates. Clear bags no larger than 12” x 12” x 6” are permissible, as well as non-transparent bags no larger than 4.5” x 6.5.” Please visit https://www.titansonline.com/stadium/bag-policy for more detailed information as well as a complete list of prohibited items. All bags and are subject to inspection by security personnel. Please note, magnetometers are in place at all points of entry.
generalInfo.childRule: Children 2 and over must have a ticket for TN Titans Football games. For CMA Music Festival: Children ages 4-14yrs must have a ticket while children 3 and under are free on parent's lap(CMA Music Festival event only).

restaurant.name: Taco Mamacita
restaurant.timings: 11 AM to 10 PM (Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Sun), 11 AM to 11 PM (Fri-Sat)

photo.caption: Enchiladas Suiza and Jalapeño Corn Slaw

review.review_text: This place is just ok for Mexican food. It is very commercial and non authentic. While I would not go back for the food, I would go for drinks. This place does have a festive vibe you can enjoy celebrating with friends and family.

The atmosphere and location are nice but the food has always been a little middle of the road for me. Service is generally a little slow but the margaritas are usually really good. I go if someone else suggests but its never on my list of places I'd pick. Not terrible, not great.
DELICIOUS!!!! Best taco place ever! Very friendly service. They have a lot of vegan and vegetarian options which made me very happy! Really great prices too!

Atmosphere: college and thirty something crowd, mostly locals. Decor: typical Mexican flare with a fun, eclectic, Nashville twist. Service:  as always, fantastic and attentive. Drinks:  very well crafted, correct amounts of liquor. Food: great choices, well prepared. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!!

Very good experience. Food was delivered quickly and was hot. I had the Sloppy Jose Taco and the Buffalo Chicken special, both of which were excellent. A must-visit if you are in Nashville. Couldn’t recommend more.
